4752,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/06\/28\/salat-no-voluntary-obligatory\/","url_meta":{"origin":12947,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Salat: No voluntary prayer when obligatory prayer begins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 28, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen the prayer commences, there is no prayer but the prescribed prayer.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 710 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim Al-Tirmidhi said, \"This was acted upon by some of the people of knowledge among the companions\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":12088,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/02\/06\/eating-dinner-maghrib-prayer\/","url_meta":{"origin":12947,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Prayer: Eating dinner before Maghrib prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 6, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIf dinner is presented close to the time of prayer, begin eating before you perform sunset prayer and do not need to rush away from your dinner.\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 640, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 558 Grade:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15928,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/09\/05\/masjid-prayer-twenty-seven-better\/","url_meta":{"origin":12947,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Jama&#8217;ah: Prayer in mosque is twenty seven times better","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 5, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cPrayer in congregation is better than prayer alone by twenty-seven degrees.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 645, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 650 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim Ibn Qudamah said, \"Congregational prayer is\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14904,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/10\/suhur-recite-fifty-ayat\/","url_meta":{"origin":12947,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Suhur: Prolonging pre-fasting meal before Fajr","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 10, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Zayd ibn Thabit reported: We ate the pre-fasting meal\u00a0with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and then we stood for prayer. It was asked, \u201cHow long was it between the two calls to prayer?\u201d Zayd said, \u201cIt was time enough to recite fifty verses from the Quran.\u201d Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25718,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/01\/09\/salat-jamaah-already-prayed\/","url_meta":{"origin":12947,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Jama&#8217;ah: Pray with congregation, even if already prayed","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 9, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Yazid ibn Al-Aswad reported: I witness the Hajj pilgrimage with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and I prayed the dawn prayer with him in the mosque of Al-Khaif. When the Prophet finished his prayer and turned around, he saw two men in the back of the people\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/12947","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=12947"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/12947\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=12947"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=12947"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=12947"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{r